================================================================================
                    GITHUB REPOSITORY SETUP GUIDE
                    Complete Step-by-Step Instructions
================================================================================

This guide will help you create and set up your GitHub repository for the
YouTube Chatbot project.

================================================================================
                         PART 1: INITIAL SETUP
================================================================================

STEP 1: Create GitHub Repository
--------------------------------
1. Go to https://github.com/new
2. Repository name: youtube-chatbot
3. Description: "An intelligent chatbot that answers questions about YouTube 
   videos using LangChain and OpenAI"
4. Make it PUBLIC (for others to use and contribute)
5. DO NOT initialize with README, .gitignore, or License (you'll add these)
6. Click "Create repository"

STEP 2: Initialize Local Repository
------------------------------------
Open terminal in your project folder and run:

git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit: YouTube Chatbot with LangChain"

STEP 3: Connect to GitHub
--------------------------
After creating the repository on GitHub, you'll see instructions. Run:

git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/youtube-chatbot.git
git push -u origin main

Replace YOUR_USERNAME with your actual GitHub username.

================================================================================
