================================================================================
                         PART 3: GITHUB SETTINGS
================================================================================

After pushing, configure your GitHub repository:

1. Go to your repository: https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/youtube-chatbot

2. Settings → General
   - Description: "An intelligent chatbot that answers questions about YouTube 
     videos using LangChain and OpenAI"
   - Website: (optional)
   - Topics: Add tags like:
     * youtube
     * chatbot
     * langchain
     * openai
     * python
     * llm
     * ai

3. Settings → Features
   ☑ Discussions    (Enable for community)
   ☑ Issues         (Enable for bug tracking)
   ☐ Wikis          (Optional)
   ☑ Projects       (Optional, for task management)

4. Settings → Code and automation
   → Actions → General
   ✓ Allow all actions and reusable workflows

5. Settings → Code and automation
   → Dependabot
   ✓ Enable version updates
   ✓ Enable security updates

6. Settings → Branches → Add branch protection rule
   - Branch name pattern: main
   - ✓ Require a pull request before merging
   - ✓ Require status checks to pass

================================================================================
                    PART 4: COMPLETE GIT WORKFLOW
================================================================================

DAILY WORKFLOW:

1. Check status
   git status

2. Add changes
   git add .
   # or specific files:
   git add filename.py

3. Commit with meaningful message
   git commit -m "feat: Add support for GPT-4"

4. Push to GitHub
   git push origin main

5. Create Pull Requests for major changes:
   git checkout -b feature/new-feature
   # Make changes
   git add .
   git commit -m "feat: Add new feature"
   git push origin feature/new-feature
   # Go to GitHub and create PR

================================================================================
                    PART 5: BRANCHES AND WORKFLOW
================================================================================

Main branches:
- main       → Production ready code
- develop    → Development branch

Feature branches:
- feature/*  → New features (feature/add-gpt4-support)
- fix/*      → Bug fixes (fix/memory-leak)
- docs/*     → Documentation (docs/update-readme)

Creating a new branch:

git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name
# or
git switch -c feature/your-feature-name

Merge changes:
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git merge feature/your-feature-name
git push origin main

Delete branch:
git branch -d feature/your-feature-name
git push origin --delete feature/your-feature-name

