================================================================================
                    USEFUL GITHUB COMMANDS
================================================================================

Clone repository:
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/youtube-chatbot.git

Check git status:
git status

View commit history:
git log
git log --oneline --graph --all

Undo changes:
git checkout .                    # Undo unstaged changes
git reset HEAD~1                  # Undo last commit (keep changes)
git revert COMMIT_HASH            # Undo specific commit

Stash changes temporarily:
git stash                         # Save changes temporarily
git stash pop                     # Restore stashed changes

Update from upstream:
git fetch origin
git rebase origin/main

Create a release:
git tag -a v1.0.0 -m "Version 1.0.0"
git push origin v1.0.0

================================================================================
                    TROUBLESHOOTING
================================================================================

Q: "fatal: remote origin already exists"
A: git remote remove origin
   Then add the correct origin

Q: "Your branch is ahead by X commits"
A: git push origin main

Q: "Merge conflict"
A: 1. Open conflicted file
   2. Edit and resolve conflicts
   3. git add .
   4. git commit -m "Resolve merge conflict"

Q: "Permission denied (publickey)"
A: Setup SSH keys:
   ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your.email@example.com"
   Add key to GitHub Settings → SSH Keys

Q: "Cannot push - need credentials"
A: Setup Personal Access Token:
   1. GitHub Settings → Developer settings → PAT
   2. Generate new token
   3. Use as password when pushing

